-- Canon to Invest $170 Million to Expand Thailand Inkjet Printer Production
-- Go Onomitsu
-- 2010-09-21T00:18:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/canon-to-invest-170-million-to-expand-thailand-inkjet-printer-production.html

          
          
             Canon Inc. plans to invest 14.6
billion yen ($170 million) to boost inkjet printer production in
Thailand. The Japanese company will begin operations at the new
facility in October 2011, according to a faxed statement today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
 gonomitsu@bloomberg.net   
 To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyung Bok Cho at 
 kcho7@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                                                 
                     
